"{\"uid\": \"artnews.com-art-news-news-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-bernini-book-morning-links-1234713028\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByThe Editors of ARTnews  The Headlines  EPIC, UNIQUE, OLYMPIC.After giving his blood, sweat, and tears for 18 months,Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of Paris's Olympics opening ceremony, the first one not to take place in a closed stadium, can be proud.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ARTnews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ARTnews\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ARTnews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ARTnews\"}, {\"begin\": 118, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9875346174804114, \"rank\": 0.01262095870132547, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.73061025139369e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His intention was to capture France in all its diversity, and it waswidely applauded there.\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999884405196643, \"rank\": 1.003376438725803e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The extravagant four-hour show, inspired by a 4.5-mile stretch of the River Seine, was divided into 12 tableaux, juxtaposing tradition and modernity.One scene, with a group of drag queenssitting along a fashion catwalk in a configuration that appeared to mimicLeonardo da Vinci'sLast Supper, has given rise to some controversy.Mike Johnson,\\u00a0a Republican who serves as the United States's Speaker of the House, called the scene \\\"shocking and insulting,\\\" and theBishops' Conferenceof Francedeplored \\\"scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 683, \"end\": 690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9999999969081728, \"rank\": 3.0881086939492015e-09, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9996348046061126, \"rank\": 0.00036298015413524433, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999977076186, \"rank\": 2.2924432499164566e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 754, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"score\": 0.9999999272354243, \"rank\": 4.2068585983533645e-08, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999190685512436, \"rank\": 8.093799877300705e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But generally, the reception was positive.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheLos Angeles Timescalled the event a \\\"unique opening ceremony in the history of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Related ArticlesFrench Culture Ministry Admits Stolen Louvre Jewels, Valued at $102 M., Are Not InsuredDrag Queen Alexis Stone Transformed into the Mona Lisa for Milan Fashion Show  SCARFACE.The Baroque sculptorBerniniwas 40 when he decided to immortalize the features of his 23-year-old mistress,Costanza Piccolomini.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2824504060630436e-14, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.315202768111037e-17, \"text\": \"Costanza\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\"}, {\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottavio_Piccolomini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.961184771238297e-25, \"text\": \"Piccolomini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottavio_Piccolomini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottavio_Piccolomini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The couple's affair was wild and intemperate.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just months after lovingly carving Costanza's bust in marble, Bernini caught wind of her sleeping with his younger brother Luigi, and ordered one of his servants to slash her face with a knife.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.315202768111037e-17, \"text\": \"Costanza\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Costanza_Piccolomini_Bonarelli\"}, {\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bernini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the shocking story thatRachel Blackmorewrites about in herupcoming book, due to be released August 1.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Blackmore started digging into Constanza's past, after hearing the presenters of a documentary make a passing remark about her disfigurement by Bernini.\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"score\": 0.881383199962492, \"rank\": 0.1308980213089845, \"text\": \"Constanza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Constan\\u021ba\"}, {\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bernini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gian_Lorenzo_Bernini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted to free Costanza from the male gaze which has clouded our view for the past 400 years,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Writing [her story] was also a way for me to examine the ways in which male coercion and violence are still used to control women today.\\\"\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 2110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Digest  TheMetropolitan Museum of Artin New York attracted more local visitors last year than it did prior to the Covid-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digest_(Roman_law)\", \"score\": 0.9997336706836197, \"rank\": 0.0002664002664003856, \"text\": \"The Digest\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digest_(Roman_law)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digest_(Roman_law)\"}, {\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999363354, \"rank\": 6.363047190414452e-11, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International numbers, on the other hand, are about half their pre-2020 figure, reflecting a broader drop in foreigners visiting the city since that year.\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[The Art Newspaper]  ThePaisley Art Institute's \\u00a31.5 million art collection, with works from the Glasgow Boys and the Scottish Colourists, will be sold off after the organization's relationship with thePaisley Museum, where the works were previously shown and held in storage, became strained.\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2521, \"end\": 2540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Colourists\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottish Colourists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Colourists\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Colourists\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[Scotsman]  The hills around Vari, 10 miles southeast of Athens, are etched with more than 2,000 graffiti from the 6th century BCE, some containing images of trireme warships, speeding horses, packs of hunting dogs.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vari\", \"score\": 0.7643127488466224, \"rank\": 0.30836493504645895, \"text\": \"Vari\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vari\"}, {\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9999981002188034, \"rank\": 1.8995422586102576e-06, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 2823, \"end\": 2826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"score\": 0.9991182750581542, \"rank\": 0.0008825030639829465, \"text\": \"BCE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Common_Era\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A new one has been discovered on a dirt track leading from the costal highway to a hilltop communication tower.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tiny graffito seems to show thepresence of a lost templeon the site of the Parthenon.\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[Artnet]  According to art historian and professorMartin Kemp, there is no case for returning theMona Lisato Italy, since the painting\\u00a0was spotted in France afterLeonardo da Vincileft Florence in 1507.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3170, \"end\": 3174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5206523002141583e-12, \"text\": \"Kemp\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\"}, {\"begin\": 3263, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999884405196643, \"rank\": 1.003376438725803e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we are to have a measured discussion of restitution, we need to get the history right,\\\" Kemp writes.\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5206523002141583e-12, \"text\": \"Kemp\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Kemp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[The Art Newspaper]  The Manhattan District Attorney's Office has announced the restitution of a 1918Egon Schielework to its rightful owners.\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3444, \"end\": 3453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999950549212769, \"rank\": 4.945103038334426e-06, \"text\": \"Manhattan\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 3444, \"end\": 3471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Yor